cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL. 

The paper focuses on image classification using deep convolutional neural networks and recurrent neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of RNNs for encoding contextual information, which falls under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper proposes two RNN models, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the integration of CNNs and HRNNs, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
